t="NO" valid="yes">Shr. V, 1, 127</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.41" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 4, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.41" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 4, 41</bibl><lb />2) a wonder, something wonderful: <cit><quote>'tis that m. and queen of gems that nature pranks her in attracts my soul,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 2.4.88" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 4, 88</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>O m. of men,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.3.33" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 3, 33</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>be not offended, nature's m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.54" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 3, 54</bibl></cit>.
